      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CLARA ROCKS (8) will find this easier than the last attempt in stronger company at Menangle. Won at the previous appearance at Penrith when she did some work early before finding the front and scoring by 3.2m. The driver has some work to do from this wide starting position but with even luck she is up to winning a race like this. KIKI MEISTER (5) was well fancied last start but manners let him down. Had been tackling stronger company prior. He is up to winning this with his A-game. FRANKIROMAR (9) is hard to knock after winning all three starts this time in, the latest in a Waratah Final at Menangle when getting home by 1.2 metres. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and if she gets the gaps could strike again. NEXT TO ME NZ (2) led for a last-start win at Tamworth and draws to be involved again.",
